description:
Join Pr. Mark Finley, along with hosts Dr. Frank Hasel and Keldie Paroshi, in our upcoming video as they unravel the biblical significance of Spiritual Gifts and Ministries—the 17th fundamental belief of the Seventh-day Adventist Church.

In this episode, part of our engaging series on the 28 Fundamental Beliefs, we explore the core teachings of Adventism. Pastor Finley, with his wealth of experience as a pastor, teacher, and evangelist, joins forces with Frank Hasel and Keldie Paroshi to explore the deep biblical meaning, beauty, and relevance of Spiritual Gifts and Ministries.

Discover the distinguishing aspects between natural talents and spiritual gifts, as well as the purpose of these gifts in building up the church and fulfilling its mission. Together, we will embark on a journey of understanding, uncovering the biblical reasons behind Adventist beliefs and the importance of spiritual gifts for the church and humanity.

Are you curious about how to identify and develop your own spiritual gifts? Join us as we discuss the practical steps to seek and discover the unique gifts bestowed upon each believer. We will also delve into the ongoing work of the Holy Spirit in the life of a faithful follower.

This video is part of our series that aims to make Adventist beliefs accessible to all, regardless of their background. Whether you're new to the church or seeking to deepen your understanding, this episode provides a valuable resource for exploring the 17th fundamental belief.

Join us on this enlightening journey as we dive into the profound depths of Adventist teachings. Don't miss this opportunity to strengthen your faith, discover your purpose, and engage with the transformative power of Spiritual Gifts and Ministries. Tune in now and be inspired to embrace your unique role in the mission of the church.
